1948,AIA,"63) Companies in the financial services sector reported the lowest levels of awareness, with limited disclosure and integration of climate risks in most markets.",2020.0
1949,AIA,This was surprising given the growing interest in disclosure structures such as the TCFD and the potential losses to companies in financial services from climate change.,2020.0
1950,AIA,"Exceptions to this trend were Australian financials, driven by local stakeholder interest in climate change disclosure.",2020.0
1951,AIA,"Other sectors, including the oil and gas sector, demonstrated a stronger understanding of climate risk issues, likely due to stakeholder interest and growing scrutiny of the climate performance of these sectors.",2020.0
1952,AIA,"The real estate sector also demonstrated strong knowledge of climate risks, particularly in markets such as Singapore and Hong Kong, where real estate companies were notable sustainability leaders.",2020.0
