4276,AXA,"Climate refers to averages of weather over longer time horizons (typically 30+ years) and low resolutions, whilst weather refers to short-term, relatively regional events.",2021.0
4277,AXA,"So, while climate change is a global phenomenon, its impacts will manifest through localized extreme weather events.",2021.0
